<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06141046 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06141046 </ACCESS><CAPTION>  Photo; PHOTO: Shannon Brace; ... Rare form of cancer  </CAPTION><DESCRIPT>  GILROY; CHILD; HOSPITAL; SURGERY; CHARITY; MONEY  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Donations to the Gift of Life Fund for Shannon Brace, the 4-year-old Gilroycancer victim who has grabbed Bay Area hearts, have topped $131,000.;    Theyoungster was stricken two years ago with a rare form of cancer.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Local  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  BONE MARROW TRANSPLANT FUND GROWS TO $131,000  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     Doctors say her only hope for survival lies in an expensive bone marrowtransplant and intensive chemotherapy that has cured people with similarcancers in 30 percent of some adult cases.;    The estimated cost is$205,000.;    Surgeons at Stanford University Hospital two weeks ago removedsome of Shannon's marrow and plan to reinject it into her body in June, afterchemotherapy that could begin by the end of May.;    Right now, Shannon isrecovering at home from surgery May 8 to remove four malignant tumors from herright lung.;    The chemotherapy will begin when she has recovered from theoperation, said her mother, Laurie Brace.;    Before her cancer, Shannon, anonly child, required 17 operations before she was 10 months old to correctkidney problems.;    She captured the media spotlight on April 14 when she wasbounced on Barbara Bush's lap as the first lady visited the new Lucile SalterPackard Children's Hospital at Stanford.;    Laurie Brace and her husband,Larry, appealed to the public for financial help in March after theirinsurance carrier refused to pay for the treatments, calling themexperimental.; IFYOU'RE INTERESTED; Donations to the non-profit Gift of Lifefor Shannon M. Brace fund, account No. 03-00-3537, can be made to WatsonvilleFederal Savings and Loan Association, 805 First St., Gilroy 95020. The taxidentification number for the account is 77-0274394.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  JACK FOLEY, Mercury News Staff Writer